      "span_text": "Covrig employs software containers  , an operating system-level virtualisation mechanism that provides the ability to run multiple isolated virtual Linux systems (\"containers\") atop a single host OS. When launched, Covrig starts by loading the selected range of revisions from the project's Git repository, and for each revision starts a new software container.",
